  },
  "_how_to_update": "After git pull on this repo (or automatically, every ~6 days, via the auto-update UserPromptSubmit hook), scripts/ai-brain-auto-update.py (cross-platform; the .sh is a thin delegator for old wirings) fast-forwards ~/.claude/skills/ai-brain-starter, runs scripts/sync-skills.py (skill content backup + overwrite), and then runs scripts/install-hooks-user-level.py ITSELF (bounded) to rewire ~/.claude/settings.json — the deploy no longer waits on Claude to run it, so a merged PR reaches the machine the same session (MYC-720). On Windows the installer rewrites these POSIX commands into the portable hook_runner form (see scripts/PORTABILITY.md section 5). The pull is ff-only: a divergent or dirty checkout is refused and surfaced for manual merge, never given a surprise merge commit. If the auto path is bypassed (pinned via ~/.claude/.ai-brain-starter-pinned, network down, hook disabled), re-run scripts/install-hooks-user-level.py or the bootstrap manually — both call the installer with --fail-on-missing so divergent-fork strands surface loudly."
}
